investigation.title: During development, the Sku5 mutant roots engage different genes than wild type WS roots, either on the ground or in spaceflight.
investigation.description: The wild type WS plants and the Sku5 mutant plants in the WS background were germinated on ISS or on the ground and the gene expression profiles in roots at 4 days or 8 days were established. The Sku5 gene (AT4G12420) codes for a multi-copper oxidase-like protein SKU5 protein that is involved in directed root tip growth.

project.funding: The work was supported by grant number GA-2013-104, Center for Advancement of Science in Space (CASIS), URL: http://www.iss-casis.org/. The funders had no role in study design, data collection and analysis, decision to publish, or preparation of the manuscript.
